{"lemma":"سَلِس","slug":"سَلِس","root":"س.ل.س","root_slug":"س-ل-س","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20411","n20412","n20414","n20415","n20416"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"docile, obedient, tame"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sociable, easygoing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"familiar"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"flexible, smooth (style)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"phlegmatic","tags":["modern"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"suffering from diabetes"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare سَلِسَ (salisa, “to be obedient, to be docile, to be smooth (style)”)."},"ipa":["/sa.lis/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20411","headword_ar":"سَلِسَ","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsapN","text_ar":"سَلَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwsapN","text_ar":"سُلُوسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, loose, not tight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slack;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the only signification indicated by ISd; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisN","text_ar":"سَلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below;) and also as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M:) [in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsapN","text_ar":"سَلَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are said to be simply substs.: see the former of these two words below.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa","text_ar":"سَلِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsapN","text_ar":"سَلَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below,)] said of a colt, (TA,) [and of a horse, and, tropically, of a man, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisN","text_ar":"سَلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, tractable, submissive, compliant, obsequious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa liY biHaq~iY","text_ar":"سَلِسَ لِى بِحَقِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was easy to me in giving me my due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa bawoluhu","text_ar":"سَلِسَ بَوْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His urine flowed involuntarily; he was unable to retain his urine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [The explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisN","text_ar":"سَلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. below will serve to give further illustrations of this verb.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"سَلِسَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-tree lost the stumps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower ends, of its branches;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolasat","text_ar":"اَسْلَسَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the epithet applied to the palm-tree in this case is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolaAsN","text_ar":"مِسْلَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or, accord. to the Tekmileh and O and L, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolisN","text_ar":"مُسْلِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it seems that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolapN musolisN","text_ar":"نَخْلَةٌ مُسْلِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a palm-tree that lets fall and strews its unripe dates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolaAsN","text_ar":"مِسْلَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that usually does thus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what falls from the palm-tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Abbád, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisati Alxa$abapu","text_ar":"سَلِسَتِ الخَشَبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The piece of wood became old and crumbling and wasted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulisa","text_ar":"سُلِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosN","text_ar":"سَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salasN","text_ar":"سَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became bereft of reason."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","TA","S","K","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n20412","headword_ar":"سلّس","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-'Abbád,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoliysN","text_ar":"تَسْلِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set, fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a composite ornament, of the ornaments worn by women, not consisting of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazar","text_ar":"خَزَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or beads]. (Ibn-'Abbád, K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n20414","headword_ar":"سَلْسٌ","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A string upon which beads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white beads worn by female slaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are strung:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwsN","text_ar":"سُلُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman's ear-drop;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman's ornament called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurT","text_ar":"قُرط"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád, K.) ―         -b2-  And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwsN","text_ar":"سُلُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women's mufflers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headcoverings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xumrN","text_ar":"خُمرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximaArN","text_ar":"خِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says IAar; and he cites as an ex.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado malaA^ato marokuw~ahaA ruw^uwsaA\n                      \n                     \n                        kaA^an~a fiyhi EujuzFA juluwsFA\n                      \n                     \n                        $umoTa Alr~uw^uwsi A^aloqati Als~uluwsaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(referring to camels)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had filled their watering-trough with heads, as though there were in it old women sitting, with grizzled heads, having thrown off the mufflers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: they having eaten of [the kind of plants, or trees, called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that their faces and heads had become white, he likens them to old women that had thrown off the mufflers. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20415","headword_ar":"سَلَسٌ","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salAsapN","text_ar":"سَلاسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said in the M to be inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa","text_ar":"سَلِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (q. v.,) and in the K to be simply substs., signify, as substs.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Looseness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteadiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easiness, gentleness, tractableness, submissiveness; compliance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obsequiousness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [Hence,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY kalaAmihi salaAsapN","text_ar":"فِى كَلَامِهِ سَلَاسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his speech is easiness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)       -A2-  For the former, see also 1: ―         -b2-  and 4."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20416","headword_ar":"سَلِسٌ","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa","text_ar":"سَلِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlisN","text_ar":"سَالِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Loose, not tight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slack;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1, first sentence;) and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a nail, (A, TA,) and to any other thing. (TA.) A rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      mamokuwrapN garovaY Alwi$aAHi Als~aAlisi\n                      \n                     \n                        taDoHaku Eano *iY A^u$ur K guDaArisi"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1405},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female of slender make, whose loose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wi$aAH","text_ar":"وِشَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"required more than it had within it to fill it, laughing so as to discover cool and sweet serrated and sharp teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a thing: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable; submissive; compliant; obsequious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) applied [to a horse and the like, and, tropically,] to a man. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN salisu AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ سَلِسُ القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse easy to be led; tractable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN salisu AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ سَلِسُ القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolaAsu","text_ar":"مِسْلَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is easy to be led,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persuaded; tractable, submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compliant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy in private conference;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saholu Alxalowapi","text_ar":"سَهْلُ الخَلْوَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b4-  Beverage, or wine,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that descends gently"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down the throat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisu Albawoli","text_ar":"سَلِسُ البَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose urine flows involuntarily; who is unable to retain his urine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","TA","S","Msb","K"]}]}}